subSubSection.paragraph:
ANTERIOR GONOPODS (
Figs 59
A–C, 60A–G). Sternal plate (
sp
) anteriorly with a well-developed, medial, hairy, subtriangular, sternal sac (
ss
). Gonopods consisting of two lateral (
lp
) [= s 
sensu
Golovatch and Makarov (2011)
: 19, fig 44] and a medial syncoxal part (
s
), these being equally high. Syncoxite wide, with a pair of lateral lobes (
lo
) anteriorly; with two pairs of shoulders (
sh1
and 
sh2
) and a quadrangular apex (
a
) distally. Lateral parts with a small lamellar structure (
ls
) laterally; postero-apically, with two small subtriangular denticles (
d1
and 
d2
) and a group of setae (
gs
) around opening (
o
). Posteriorly, with coxal vesicles (
cv
) and two longitudinal rows of setae (
rs
).
